To make a folder hidden (Windows):
* Open File Explorer from the taskbar.
* Navigate to the directory containing the folder you wish to hide
* Right Click the folder you wish to hide and select Preferences
* On the Preferences window, remaining in the General tab, click the "Hidden" checkbox to toggle it to "on".
* You'll know you've succeeded if the folder disappears/becomes semi-transparent

Making Hidden Folders viewable/hidden:
* Open File Explorer from the taskbar.
* Select View > Options > Change folder and search options.
* Select the View tab and, in Advanced settings, toggle "Show hidden files, folders, and drives" to the desired setting and press OK.

Note that when you open a file, it may show up in the Quick Access section of a new Explorer window- Simply right click the offending files and select "Remove From Quick Access" from the offending file(s). A similar thing may happen in the folder view to the left, next to your pins- Use exactly the same process there. Once you've opened it once, it won't show back up in Quick Access again.
